# Urban,ShelveLoc,US are qualitative 

corr = round(cor(Carseats[c(-7,-10,-11)]),1)
ggcorrplot(corr, hc.order = TRUE, type = "upper",lab=TRUE)

# Linear Regression . 

qlm.fit = lm(Sales ~ .,data = Carseats)

summary(qlm.fit)
